                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         String exclusionTimezone)
        Constructor used by JMX for creating the interest schedule object. The start and end times are used along with the days so as to time box when interests (and then events) are created. If the current time and day of the system is outside the boxed time below then the event is created by ESPER, but ultimately not propagated along the escalation path.
        Parameters:
        enabled - whether the schedule is enabled
        range - whether this schedule object represents a range
        rangeType - range type
        startCron - the starting Cron entry
        startTimezone - the timezone of the start time
        endTimezone - the timezone of the end time
        startTime - the start time
        endTime - the end time
        startDate - the start date
        endDate - the end date
        endDaysLater - integer indicating the day offset of the end time from the start time
        recurDays - days of the week on which a weekly schedule recurrs
        recurrenceStartDate - the date on which the recurrence is to start
        recurrenceEndDate - the date on which the recurrence is to end
        exclusionsEnabled - exclusions enabled
        excludedDates - exclusion dates
        exclusionTimezone - exclusion timezone
